Orlando pirates fans will today hold a protest in Vosloorus to express their anger at the police s lack of progress in bringing to book captain Senzo Meyiwa s killer.Prominent club supporter Phillip Jwara said thousands are expected to converge at the Vosloorus Stadium from where the march to the local police station will begin this morning.There is pressure mounting on police to arrest the killers of the late Meyiwa in the wake of the second anniversary of the player s death. Even though the murder took place more than two years ago, the pain in our hearts is still fresh. Our wounds will never heal, Jwara said.Meyiwa was shot by unknown people while visiting the home of the mother of his child, singer Kelly Khumalo, in Vosloorus, Johannesburg two years ago.TNA Reporter &nbsp;